# =============================================================================
# BagrutProject — .gitignore
# Project: Predicting Israeli High School Bagrut Success Using Socioeconomic Data
# Authors: Yousef Shehade & Shada Esawi
#
# Goal: a lean, reproducible repository. Raw source data and course material are
# excluded (kept on local disk only); the modular step pipelines regenerate every
# intermediate artifact. External data links are documented in the step READMEs.
# =============================================================================

# ── Raw source datasets (NOT redistributed — see step_1 / step_2 READMEs) ──────
datasets/
israel_bagrut_averages.csv
downloadFile.xlsx
# Any raw spreadsheet dropped directly in the repo root
/*.csv
/*.xlsx
/*.xls

# ── Large regenerable intermediate caches (rebuilt by running the step scripts) ─
# Small aggregated summaries (ses_clean, budget_clean, city_mapping_log,
# school_level_*, cleaned_modeling_ready, models/*) ARE tracked; these full-size
# merge tables (7-21 MB) are regenerated on demand by running the step scripts.
step_1_ingestion_standardization/data/bagrut_clean.csv
step_2_data_merging_integration/data/merged_three_datasets.csv

# Same two caches, preserved under their v1 (pre-rebuild) paths in archive/ —
# archive/ is kept as a reference/audit trail, not to bloat the repo with data
# that was never tracked even when these were the live pipeline steps.
archive/v1_two_dataset_pipeline/step_1_ingestion_standardization/data/bagrut_clean.csv
archive/v1_two_dataset_pipeline/step_2_data_merging_integration/data/merged_bagrut_ses.csv

# ── Course material (presentations & lecturer guidelines) ──────────────────────
*.pptx
*.docx
*.doc
PRESENTATIONS/
guidelines/

# ── Python housekeeping ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.env
.venv/
venv/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ── OS / editor cruft ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
